---
// We'll treat the Privacy Policy as a "Security Log"
const lastUpdated = "February 12, 2026";
---
    <main class="pt-32 lg:pt-48 pb-24">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
            
            <div class="border-b-2 border-black pb-12 mb-16">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                    <span class="font-mono text-[#A53029] text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.5em]">// Protocol_Ref: PRIV-2026</span>
                    <div class="h-[1px] w-12 bg-gray-200"></div>
                </div>
                <h1 class="font-heading text-6xl lg:text-8xl uppercase tracking-tighter leading-none mb-8">
                    Privacy <span class="italic text-transparent stroke-black">Policy</span>
                </h1>
                <p class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400">
                    Last Modified: {lastUpdated} // Status: Active
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="prose prose-zinc max-w-none 
                prose-h2:font-heading prose-h2:uppercase prose-h2:text-3xl prose-h2:tracking-tight prose-h2:mt-16 prose-h2:mb-8
                prose-p:font-sans prose-p:text-gray-600 prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-p:mb-6
                prose-ul:font-sans prose-ul:text-gray-600">
                
                <p class="lead text-xl text-black font-medium italic border-l-4 border-[#A53029] pl-6 my-10">
                    At Global Music Solutions (GMS), we treat your data with the same precision we apply to royalty cue sheets. This document outlines our data handling protocols.
                </p>

                <h2>1. Data Collection // Input</h2>
                <p>
                    We collect information that identifies, relates to, or could reasonably be linked with you. This includes:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Identifiers:</strong> Name, email address, and IP address.</li>
                    <li><strong>Professional Data:</strong> Company name and music industry affiliations.</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> How you navigate our digital interface and technical reports.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>2. Utilization // Processing</h2>
                <p>
                    Your data is processed to ensure the highest output of our services. We use it to:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Provide and maintain our global music administration tools.</li>
                    <li>Communicate updates regarding industry news and technical insights.</li>
                    <li>Verify quality assurance across our international methodology.</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>3. Encryption // Security</h2>
                <p>
                    We implement industry-standard encryption to protect your information. While no digital transmission is 100% secure, our methodology includes multi-layer verification to mitigate risks of unauthorized access.
                </p>

                <h2>4. Third-Party Signal Sharing</h2>
                <p>
                    GMS does not sell your data. We only share information with proven partners (such as Performing Rights Organizations or technical infrastructure providers) when necessary to execute our core services.
                </p>

                <h2>5. User Rights // Control</h2>
                <p>
                    You have the right to request access to the data we hold or request its deletion. For any inquiries regarding your digital footprint within our systems, please contact our data dispatcher.
                </p>

                <div class="mt-24 p-12 bg-zinc-50 border border-gray-100 flex flex-col items-center text-center">
                    <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-gray-400 mb-4">Inquiry Terminal</span>
                    <a href="/contact" class="font-heading text-2xl uppercase underline hover:text-[#A53029] transition-colors">
                        Contact Data Officer
                    </a>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer class="py-12 border-t border-gray-100 text-center">
        <p class="font-mono text-[9px] uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-300">
            Global Music Solutions // Rights & Privacy Dept.
        </p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>

<style is:global>
    :root {
        --font-heading: 'Oswald', sans-serif;
        --font-sans: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    }
    .font-heading { font-family: var(--font-heading); }
    .font-sans { font-family: var(--font-sans); }
    .font-mono { font-family: var(--font-mono); }
    .stroke-black { -webkit-text-stroke: 1px black; }
</style>